"title": "5737: sisters",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5737: sisters",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The daughter of one's parents, or of either mother or father. The relationship with a sister is a close one, especially with an unmarried sister.</p>\n<h2>The relationship with a sister was a close one</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:25\">EZK 44:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:1-Lev21:3\">LEV 21:1–21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:6-Num6:7\">NUM 6:6–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:1-Job1:4\">JOB 1:1–1:4</a></p>\n<h2>A brother had some measure of responsibility for his sister</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:8-Song8:9\">SNG 8:8–8:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:28-Gen24:60\">GEN 24:28–24:60</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:19-2Sam13:20\">2SA 13:19–13:20</a></p>\n<h2>Sexual relationships with sisters</h2>\n<h3>Marrying a sister was permissible in pre-Mosaic times</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:12\">GEN 20:12</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Sexual relationships with a sister were later forbidden in Mosaic law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:9\">LEV 18:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:11-Lev18:13\">LEV 18:11–18:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:18\">LEV 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:17\">LEV 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:22\">DEU 27:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:11\">EZK 22:11</a></p>\n<h3>Rape</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:1-Gen34:31\">GEN 34:1–34:31</a> <em>Dinah's rape was avenged by her brothers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:1-2Sam13:19\">2SA 13:1–13:19</a> <em>Tamar was raped by her half-brother</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:23-2Sam13:36\">2SA 13:23–13:36</a> <em>Absalom avenged Tamar's rape.</em></p>\n<h2>Sometimes the wives of the patriarchs posed as their sisters</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:13\">GEN 20:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:10-Gen12:20\">GEN 12:10–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:7\">GEN 20:1–20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:1-Gen26:10\">GEN 26:1–26:10</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the behaviour of sisters</h2>\n<h3>Jealousy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:1\">GEN 30:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:7-Gen30:8\">GEN 30:7–30:8</a></p>\n<h3>Criticism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:38-Luke10:42\">LUK 10:38–10:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:1-Num12:15\">NUM 12:1–12:15</a></p>\n<h3>Kindness and concern</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:11\">2CH 22:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:2\">2KI 11:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1-Exod2:8\">EXO 2:1–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:11\">JOB 42:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:1-John11:3\">JHN 11:1–11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:17-John11:32\">JHN 11:17–11:32</a></p>\n<h2>Sisters-in-law</h2>\n<h3>Marriage to a sister-in-law was allowed in specific circumstances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:5-Deut25:10\">DEU 25:5–25:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:6-Gen38:11\">GEN 38:6–38:11</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual relationships with sisters-in-law were forbidden under normal circumstances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:16\">LEV 18:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:21\">LEV 20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:17-Mark6:20\">MRK 6:17–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:19-Luke3:20\">LUK 3:19–3:20</a></p>\n<h2>Sister used as a term of affection</h2>\n<h3>By a husband</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:9-Song4:10\">SNG 4:9–4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:12\">SNG 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:1-Song5:2\">SNG 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>In the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:1\">ROM 16:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1-1Tim5:2\">1TI 5:1–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:1-Phlm1:2\">PHM 1:1–1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:15-Jas2:17\">JAS 2:15–2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:13\">2JN 1:13</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of sister</h2>\n<h3>Of death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:13-Job17:16\">JOB 17:13–17:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Of wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:1-Prov7:5\">PRO 7:1–7:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Of nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:6-Jer3:10\">JER 3:6–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:44-Ezek16:63\">EZK 16:44–16:63</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:1-Ezek23:49\">EZK 23:1–23:49</a></p>\n<h2>Sister as a theological term</h2>\n<h3>Describing the relationship of believers to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:46-Matt12:50\">MAT 12:46–12:50</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:31-Mark3:35\">MRK 3:31–3:35</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ requires his followers to put him before family ties</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:26\">LUK 14:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:29\">MAT 19:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:29-Mark10:30\">MRK 10:29–10:30</a></p>",
